#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.92"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.92:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.92:0.2"
msgid "9. Theravagga "
msgstr "9. Senior Mendicants "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.92:0.3"
msgid "92. Dutiyarāhulasutta "
msgstr "92. Rāhula (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn22.92:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.92:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā rāhulo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Seated to one side, Rāhula said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.92:1.3"
msgid "“kathaṃ nu kho, bhante, jānato kathaṃ passato imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānāpagataṃ mānasaṃ hoti vidhāsamatikkantaṃ santaṃ suvimuttan”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, how does one know and see so that the mind is rid of ego, possessiveness, and conceit for this conscious body and all external stimuli; and going beyond discrimination, it’s peaceful and well freed?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.137, sc2
msgctxt "sn22.92:2.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ kiñci, rāhula, rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā … pe … yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ rūpaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā anupādā vimutto hoti. "
msgstr "“Rāhula, when one truly sees any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: *all* form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self,’ one is freed by not grasping. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.92:2.2"
msgid "Yā kāci vedanā … "
msgstr "One truly sees any kind of feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.92:2.3"
msgid "yā kāci saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.92:2.4"
msgid "ye keci saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.92:2.5"
msgid "yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā anupādā vimutto hoti. "
msgstr "When one truly sees any kind of consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: *all* consciousness—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self,’ one is freed by not grasping. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.92:2.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, rāhula, jānato evaṃ passato imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānāpagataṃ mānasaṃ hoti vidhāsamatikkantaṃ santaṃ suvimuttan”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how to know and see so that the mind is rid of ego, possessiveness, and conceit for this conscious body and all external stimuli; and going beyond discrimination, it’s peaceful and well freed.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.92:2.7"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.92:2.8"
msgid "Theravaggo catuttho. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn22.92:3.1"
msgid "Ānando tisso yamako, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.92:3.2"
msgid "anurādho ca vakkali; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.92:3.3"
msgid "Assaji khemako channo, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn22.92:3.4"
msgid "rāhulā apare duve. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
